sec.p:
For patients for whom the clinician assessed the rabies risk, we estimated the agreement between the risk category assigned by clinicians and the independently assessed risk based on the NRMG, using the weighted Cohen’s kappa statistic for ordinal variables and equal weights. Thirdly, we performed logistic regression to evaluate potential factors associated with “agreement” between the clinician and the NRMG risk assessment. A binary variable “agreement” (0: disagreement between clinician and the NRMG, 1: agreement between clinician and the NRMG) was created. Variables evaluated in the bivariate model were:


- gender;

- professional experience (number of years);

- designation of the clinician: medical doctor, assistant clinical officer, health assistant;

- highest level of qualification: Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS), Diploma or Certificate;

- health center type: Basic Health Unit, district hospital, regional referral hospital;

- district (9 levels);

- actual level of risk of the exposure event according to the NRMG (none, moderate, severe).
